### DEMO 1: Basic Send with Fluent API
### Simple order send without any special configuration
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders/simple
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "ORD-001",
  "customerId": "CUST-123",
  "amount": 299.99,
  "status": "PENDING",
  "timestamp": "2024-11-15T10:30:00"
}

###

### DEMO 2: Send with Quality of Service (QoS) Settings
### Priority order with TTL (5 min), priority level 9, and 1 second delivery delay
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders/priority
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "ORD-002",
  "customerId": "CUST-456",
  "amount": 1599.99,
  "status": "PROCESSING",
  "timestamp": "2024-11-15T14:45:00"
}

###

### DEMO 3: Send with Custom Headers/Metadata
### Order with additional metadata headers (region parameter adds tracking info)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders/with-metadata?region=US-WEST
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "ORD-003",
  "customerId": "CUST-789",
  "amount": 749.50,
  "status": "PENDING",
  "timestamp": "2024-11-15T16:20:00"
}

###

### DEMO 4: Synchronous Receive with Timeout
### Receive a message from the queue (blocks up to 5 seconds waiting for a message)
### Returns 200 with order if message available, or 204 No Content if queue is empty
GET http://localhost:8080/api/orders/receive

###

### DEMO 5: Receive and Convert (Type-Safe Retrieval)
### Same as Demo 4 but demonstrates the cleaner receive(Order.class) approach
### This is handled by the same endpoint - the service method shows the simplified pattern
GET http://localhost:8080/api/orders/receive

###

### DEMO 6: Request-Reply Pattern (Synchronous RPC)
### Send order for processing and wait for processed response
### Demonstrates synchronous request-response messaging pattern
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders/process
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "ORD-006",
  "customerId": "CUST-999",
  "amount": 2499.99,
  "status": "PENDING",
  "timestamp": "2024-11-15T18:00:00"
}

###

### DEMO 7: Reusable Operation Handle (Bulk Operations)
### Sends multiple express orders using a pre-configured reusable handle
### Demonstrates performance optimization for repetitive messaging
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders/bulk-express

###